{"id":4070,"title":"[Professor Dong Gui-rong's experiences in treatment of child cerebral palsy].","abstract":"According to the characteristics of the etiology and pathogenesis of child cerebral palsy, on the basis of \"regulating the mind in treatment of all kinds of diseases\" and \"regulating the functions of five zang organs with back-shu points\", Professor DONG Gui-rong applied the penetrating needling technique on the scalp points and acupuncture at back-shu points of five zang organs in the treatment of child cerebral palsy. The valuable clinical experiences have been summarized as \"regulating the mind with scalp needling technique, benefiting the brain and opening the orifice\", \"regulating five zang organs with back-shu points\" and \"integration of acupuncture and rehabilitation, and function reconstruction\". Two effective cases were introduced.","date":"2014-12-15","categories":"Nervous System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25509746","annotations":[{"name":"Acupuncture","weight":0.818037,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acupuncture"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.797998,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Etiology","weight":0.795167,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Etiology"},{"name":"Organ (anatomy)","weight":0.795008,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organ_(anatomy)"},{"name":"Physical therapy","weight":0.723856,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_therapy"},{"name":"Brain","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain"},{"name":"Cerebral palsy","weight":0.713452,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerebral_palsy"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.651095,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Child","weight":0.522715,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Child"},{"name":"Mind","weight":0.482994,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mind"},{"name":"Cerebrum","weight":0.482424,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerebrum"},{"name":"Pathogenesis","weight":0.453394,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogenesis"},{"name":"Professor","weight":0.39024,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Professor"},{"name":"Anus","weight":0.131422,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anus"},{"name":"Scalp","weight":0.115795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scalp"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.113674,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Palsy","weight":0.0223718,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palsy"},{"name":"Tibetan people","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tibetan_people"},{"name":"DONG Energy","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DONG_Energy"},{"name":"Guifang","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guifang"},{"name":"Function (mathematics)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Function_(mathematics)"}]}
